name: autopep8
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "autopep8" %}
{% set version = "1.7.0" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ca9b1a83e53a7fad65d731dc7a2a2d50aa48f43850407c59f6a1a306c4201142

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - autopep8 = autopep8:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - pycodestyle >=2.8
    - toml

test:
  imports:
    - autopep8
  commands:
    - pip check
    - autopep8 --help
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/hhatto/autopep8
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: MIT
  summary: A tool that automatically formats Python code to conform to the PEP 8 style guide
  dev_url: https://github.com/hhatto/autopep8

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
    - ocefpaf
